alled downsizing. At every epoch in the universe, there are low-mass\ngalaxies actively forming stars, while more massive galaxies form their stars\nover a shorter period of time within half the age of the universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Aug 2011 07:54:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 22 Jun 2012 02:28:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-15"}
